               Digit[] inputdata,
               int outputAmount,
               int functionSet,
               boolean print,
               int levelsBack,
               int mu,
               int lambda)
        Constructs a CGP Network with the given values
        Parameters:
        mutationrate - how much an Individual can be changed during one mutation
        nodeAmount - the Amount of Nodes in the net
        generationLimit - the maximum number of allowed generations
        inputdata - the InputData used for Evaluation
        outputAmount - the number of Output the Network can possess (currently only 1 or 4 (if boolean))
        functionSet - the FunctionSet that the nodes can use (1-4 and 5 for boolean)
        print - if the net is allowed to print to console during Calculation
        levelsBack - the levels-Back value the Individual should obey to
        mu - defines the (mu + lambda) - Strategy
        lambda - defines the (mu + lambda) - Strategy
